# TailwindCSS Rules

## Core Principles
- Always use Tailwind classes for styling HTML elements
- Avoid using CSS files or inline styles
- Use utility-first approach for consistent design
- Prefer Tailwind classes over custom CSS solutions

## Class Organization

### Class Order Convention
Follow this order for better readability:
1. Layout (display, position, top, right, bottom, left)
2. Flexbox/Grid (flex, grid, justify, align, etc.)
3. Spacing (margin, padding)
4. Sizing (width, height)
5. Typography (font, text, leading, tracking)
6. Visual (background, border, shadow, opacity)
7. Misc (cursor, overflow, z-index, etc.)

```tsx
// Good: Organized class order
<div className="flex items-center justify-between p-4 w-full bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg shadow-sm cursor-pointer hover:bg-gray-50">
```

### Conditional Classes
- Use template literals for dynamic classes
- Consider using `clsx` or `cn` utility for complex conditions
- Avoid ternary operators in className when possible

```tsx
// Good: Using template literals
<div className={`px-4 py-2 rounded ${isActive ? 'bg-blue-500 text-white' : 'bg-gray-100 text-gray-800'}`}>

// Better: Using cn utility (if available)
<div className={cn(
  'px-4 py-2 rounded',
  isActive ? 'bg-blue-500 text-white' : 'bg-gray-100 text-gray-800'
)}>

// Good: Simple conditions
<button className={`btn ${disabled ? 'opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed' : 'hover:bg-blue-600'}`}>
```

## Responsive Design
- Use mobile-first approach
- Apply breakpoint prefixes: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`, `2xl:`
- Stack responsive classes logically

```tsx
// Good: Mobile-first responsive design
<div className="w-full md:w-1/2 lg:w-1/3 p-4 md:p-6 lg:p-8">
```

## Color Usage
- Use semantic color names when possible
- Leverage design system tokens
- Use opacity modifiers for variants: `bg-blue-500/20`

```tsx
// Good: Semantic colors
<div className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground">
<div className="text-destructive bg-destructive/10">

// Good: Opacity modifiers
<div className="bg-black/50 text-white/90">
```

## Spacing and Sizing
- Use consistent spacing scale (4, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24, 32, etc.)
- Prefer spacing utilities over arbitrary values
- Use logical spacing (px, py, mx, my) for efficiency

```tsx
// Good: Consistent spacing
<div className="p-4 m-2 gap-4">
<div className="px-6 py-4 mx-auto">

// Avoid: Arbitrary values when utilities exist
<div className="p-[17px]"> // Use p-4 instead
```

## Typography
- Use type scale consistently
- Apply proper line heights with text sizes
- Use font weight modifiers appropriately

```tsx
// Good: Typography scale
<h1 className="text-3xl font-bold leading-tight">
<p className="text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
<span className="text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground">
```

## Layout Patterns

### Flexbox
- Use flex utilities for common layouts
- Combine with gap for spacing

```tsx
// Good: Flex layouts
<div className="flex items-center justify-between gap-4">
<div className="flex flex-col space-y-4">
<div className="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
```

### Grid
- Use CSS Grid for complex layouts
- Leverage auto-fit and auto-fill

```tsx
// Good: Grid layouts
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
<div className="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr_auto] gap-4 items-center">
```

## Interactive States
- Always include hover states for interactive elements
- Use focus states for accessibility
- Implement active states for buttons

```tsx
// Good: Interactive states
<button className="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-500 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-600 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:ring-offset-2 active:bg-blue-700 disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed">
```

## Common Patterns

### Card Components
```tsx
<div className="bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-6">
  <div className="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
    <h3 className="text-lg font-semibold">Card Title</h3>
  </div>
  <p className="text-gray-600">Card content</p>
</div>
```

### Form Elements
```tsx
<div className="space-y-4">
  <div>
    <label className="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1">
      Label
    </label>
    <input
      className="w-full px-3 py-2 border border-gray-300 rounded-md focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:border-transparent"
      type="text"
    />
  </div>
</div>
```

### Loading States
```tsx
<div className="flex items-center justify-center p-8">
  <div className="animate-spin rounded-full h-8 w-8 border-b-2 border-primary"></div>
</div>
```

## Performance Tips
- Use `@apply` directive sparingly in CSS files
- Prefer utility classes over custom CSS
- Leverage JIT mode for optimal bundle size
- Remove unused classes with purging

## Customization
- Extend theme in `tailwind.config.js` when needed
- Use CSS custom properties for dynamic values
- Create component variants through configuration
